                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3080a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-25T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 25, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Department is with difficulty restraining responsible press comment here on
                    the Tientsin affair and is doubtful how long it may be able to do so owing to
                    the numerous circumstantial reports arriving in the United States through papers
                    published in China and Japan. An early settlement of the question is highly
                    desirable. I have spoken to Ishii in the same sense.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
